author: sussman
msg: * CHANGES:  summarize logs up to r1860

author: kfogel
msg: Greg Stein got an extra blank line when he committed a change
consisting only of a file deletion.  Heh.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/trace-commit.c
(close_edit): If didn't send any text deltas, don't print the
newline whose only purpose is to follow "Transmitting ...".

author: kfogel
msg: Philip Martin is running a pre-release GCC, and saw warnings about
variables not matching format codes:
* subversion/tests/libsvn_fs/fs-test.c
(file_integrity_helper): Declare loop variable j as svn_revnum_t.
(validate_revisions): Take a non-incremented max_rev argument
instead of num_revs, loop over revisions not integers.
(check_all_revisions): Declare revision_count as svn_revnum_t
instead of int.  Increment it after calling validate_revisions.
(merging_commit): Declare revision_count as svn_revnum_t here too,
for consistency, although it doesn't really matter.

author: kfogel
msg: * subversion/mod_dav_svn/log.c
(dav_svn__log_report): Remove references to lbr.pool, missed in
revision 1856.  Committing now, then building shared to make sure
the fix works.  Thanks to Philip Martin for the quick notice.

author: sussman
msg: Tweaks to our fs dumpfile producer.
* fs_dumprestore.txt (Content-length):  change some field names.
* dump.c : change some field names.
(dump_node): oops, fix some formatting.  and switch some
incorrect words around.  take a buffer for writing out text contents.
(svn_repos_dump_fs):  for formality, write out root-directory of rev 0.
(struct edit_baton): add reusable buffer for dumping file contents
of size
(get_dump_editor): set value of eb->bufsize.
(delete_entry, add_directory, add_file, open_file, change_dir_prop):
update callers of dump_node.
